Multi-Fill
Multi-fill filling operations are conducted in the Fill Room.  Multi-fill is the direct feed of butane from the outdoor storage tanks (2 x 10,000 gallons).  Butane is fed through process piping to a gas-filling cabinet.  The entire system, including the gas-filling cabinet, is pressurized to approximately 110 PSI and butane is directly injected into aluminum tubes.  Manually adjustable regulators are in place to prevent over-pressurization.

Other activities include:
A?    Flint packaging; 
A?    Refillable butane lighter packaging; 
A?    Raw material and finished product storage; 
A?    Machine shop (equipment and parts repair)

The facility uses Isobutane and Liquefied Petroleum, which are regulated under 40 Code of Federal Regulations (CFR) Part 68, the U.S. EPA RMP Rule.  

The majority of the flammable materials are either stored in aboveground storage tanks (AST) located on the southwest corner of the property or in the concrete vault aboveground storage tank (AST), located partially below gradient on the west side of the building.  These flammable materials include:
A?    Isobutane (A-31) Two (2) 10,000 gallon ASTs; 
A?    Liquefied petroleum gas (A-70) One (1) 1,850 gallon AST; 
A?    Petroleum Naphtha 15,000 gallon and Mineral Spirits 5,000 gallon -- One (1) 20,000 gallon AST A? partitioned concrete vault.
